Premier Phumulo Masualle has fired his longest serving accounting officer, Bea Hackula. Hackula was working as the superintendent-general in the cooperative governance and traditional affairs (Cogta) department.She was served with a letter of suspension in April by the premier. The office of the premier s chief of staff Nandi Sikutshwa yesterday confirmed that Hackula had been fired. In fact, she was given a hearing. There was a disciplinary process which was instituted by the premier, said Sikutshwa.For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions